,Not Recommended,287600,15995899,"Posted: 25 May, 2015",all,TRAVisty James | TSE,"6.5/10this was a hard one to ratei personally really like it when games try to take on a serious issue in an imaginative approach. sunset did an excellent job of submersing the player into a world surrounded by conflict, taking an unusual passive approach. having the player in the role of a housekeeper was a brilliant way to put the player in the shoes of a civilian, even in times of war responsibilities must be kept. i wan to see more games attempt this.however the inescapable truth was that this game was about twice as long as it really should be, to the point where i just kept asking myself ""is this ever going to end?"". i put in around 6 hours, and for a story like this it really should have been more like 2. and the price didn't justify the content. i see that there's some replayability in the story, but i was so exhausted by the end that i simply didn't have the time or the patience.in summary:this game should have been 1/2 as long and 1/4 the price6.5/10"
