,Not Recommended,287600,23131655,"Posted: 21 May, 2016",all,"God, owner of the Universe","THIS GAME SCORES [*0* | 1 | 2] = ~17% (0%-33%)Since I couldn't really play it, I can't say if it would be 1of4 or 2of4, so I'll just give it a 1of3.Got this at 90% off (->2€) but still refunded it. Reason: Broken interface. (Most of the 31 minutes game time were spent changing options and contacting the devs via their website.)Maybe (or maybe not) Sunset is a great creation on some level, but the devs failed the interfacetoo damn hardfor me to ever find out. Therefore, I rather don't force myself through this and choose to ""send them a message"".BROKEN MOUSE CONTROLMouse speed depends on frame rate (so, even depends on where you look). If you look up and pull the mouse down quickly, you end up looking straight ahead, but if you do it slowly, you end up at the bottom, so this is absolutely not a mouse acceleration issue. (Even if so, whose fault would that be.)Something is just really really broken with the mouse controls. The horz/vert mouse speed options are effective, but the speed is much too inconsistent, so it's not remotely a working fix.Another problem: In the optional very cool 2.5D mode which prevents converging vertical lines (Photographers know what I mean.) which I would really like to use, the vertical mouse speed is always at max while you stand still, but is at whatever you set it to while you walk around. Bro-ken!The game otherwise looks very good, has FOV slider with wide range, etc. - one would think that all is well, but the mouse control isprimary, it's what connects me to (or keeps me away from) a 3D 1st person game world, and it's justto damn brokenin this case.That's why I suggest to stay the hell away from this game."
